"""Cavern prop sprites: floor debris (b495-501) + room contents (b497-500).

Pixel-art props stamped onto the drawn cavern by the procedural
renderer (cavern_render.py).

CAVERN_PROPS -- ambient debris scattered on PLAIN floors. b501: the
debris-sheet-2 groups (rubble, bricks, pottery, bones, skulls, cloth,
mushrooms, moss, crystals, chains, wood, dust) are re-keyed from a
magenta re-render of the sheet -- clean chroma edges, zero
checkerboard halo. Skeleton/stalag/goo/web still come from the
defringed checkerboard sheet 1. Capped 40px.

ROOM_PROPS -- identity props per THEMED room type at a seeded
off-center spot; U/D centered fixtures; E nothing; M glyph-only.
Capped 48px.

Debris deliberately excludes anything that reads as LOOT so
decorations never bait a tap; room props deliberately INCLUDE
reward-ish art (chests) because those rooms ARE interactable.
"""

